carrots, potatoes and leeks and chop <b>4 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Add water, vegetable stock paste, nutmeg, salt and pepper, set Varoma in position and cook <b>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Set Varoma aside."},{"content":"Add spinach and cream to mixing bowl, cook <b>3 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>, then blend <b>30 sec\/speed 10<b>. Adjust seasoning to taste."},{"content":"Cut savoury egg custard into diamond shapes using spatula. Serve soup hot, topped with pieces of custard."}],"hintsAndTricks":["<i>‘Eierstich’, or savoury egg custard, is a traditional German garnish for clear soups, and is often served in ‘Hochzeitssuppe’ (wedding soup). Added to the smooth and tasty spinach and potato soup in this recipe, the melt-in-your-mouth egg custard transforms the dish into a rich treat that children and adults alike can enjoy as a starter or main dish.<\/i>","As an alternative to savoury egg custard, steam meatballs or diced smoked pork in the Varoma and serve as garnish for the soup.<br>- Savoury egg custard can be prepared as a topping for any soup."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","45m","6 portions"]}